"It's not you, it's me," a man may shrug while hiding the true reason why they are calling it quits. Or maybe one day he ghosts you and goes to alien territory leaving you in wonder, as to what really transpired.  

While everyone has a break-up style, many men dump women by avoiding to speak as to the real reason they are walking away. They feel that the woman might not understand their reason and so would rather come up with something less painful or believable.  

Four men share why they hid the true reasons for a breakup.  

She was more into the celebrity circuit, I wasn't 

Victor Walwe, 30 years, a Salesperson 






Victor Walwe, 30 years, Salesperson, Nairobi. 
Photo credit: Pool

 

"I met Hannah through a mutual friend. She was beautiful and smart, those girls you meet and start thinking of Bollywood movies, and imagine the two of you on the beach playing with your beautiful daughter. 

We dated for close to a year before I felt "this is really not working out" We differed on what I would term as ideological differences. I love talking about real issues, BBI, Curfew, and other issues. Am the type of guy that would be interested in talking about author Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie the whole day. Hannah enjoyed having conversations about celebrities, the likes of Diamond, Femi One, and someone called Samidoh. 

We couldn't find a common ground and decided I had had enough of trying to keep up with Diamond's life. After close to a year, I cut off communication, ignored her calls, and did not call or text her back. We eventually drifted apart and parted ways. I could not have told her the actual reason for the silence because she would have possibly not believed me.  



